  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "However, the changes in these parameters were not significant in the Qiju group with only 3.71% (95% CI: -4.98% to 14.63%), 4.98% (95% CI: -9.06% to 13.47%), 6.81% (95% CI: -1.36% to 17.68%), and 8.84% (95% CI: -1.46% to 19.92%) decrease in the percentage of estimate MMEF, FEF 75, FEF 50, and FEF 25, respectively, at lag 1 week (Figure 4).",
    "As shown in Figure 5, no parameters of lung function were statistically significant between the Qiju group and the control group at baseline.",
    "The difference in lung function parameters between these two groups became greater, and the trend to provide lung health benefits tended to increase in the Qiju group in the 2nd and 4th weeks.",
    "However, there were no statistical differences in all time periods (Figure 5).",
    "In this randomized trial among healthy young adults in Hangzhou, China, we examine lung function benefits of Qiju granules against PM 2.5 exposure at different time periods occurring at lag intervals of 0, 1, or 0-1 week before health examination, which include large airways function (FVC, FEV 1, and PEF) and small airways function (MMEF, FEF 75, FEF 50, and FEF 25)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "However, the changes in these parameters were not significant in the Qiju group with only 3.71% (95% CI: -4.98% to 14.63%), 4.98% (95% CI: -9.06% to 13.47%), 6.81% (95% CI: -1.36% to 17.68%), and 8.84% (95% CI: -1.46% to 19.92%) decrease in the percentage of estimate MMEF, FEF 75, FEF 50, and FEF 25, respectively, at lag 1 week (Figure 4)."
